Fields.TU: Line 1 Wages, salaries and tips. This should be shown in box 1 of your Form(s) W-2.
Line 2 Taxable interest. If the total is over $1,500, you cannot use Form 1040 E Z.
Line 3 Unemployment compensation and Alaska Permanent Fund dividends.
Line 4 Add lines 1, 2, and 3. This is your adjusted gross income.
Line 5. If no one can claim you (or your spouse if a joint return), enter $10,000 if single; $20,000 if married filing jointly.
6 Subtract line 5 from line 4. If line 5 is larger than line 4, enter6 Subtract line 4 from line 4. If line 5 is larger than line 4, enter zero.  This is your taxable income.
Line 7. Federal income tax withheld from Forms W-2 and 1099.
Line 9. Add lines 7 and 8a. These are your total payments and credits.
Line 10. Tax. Use the amount on line 6 above to find your tax in the tax table in the instructions. Then, enter the tax from the table on this line.
Line 11a. If line 9 is larger than line 10, subtract line 10 from line 9. This is your refund.
Line 12. If line 10 is larger than line 9, subtract line 9 from line 10. This is the amount you owe. For details on how to pay, see instructions.
